Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo Osun State Government has said it would monitor pupils in public schools in the state relying on technology. It added that plans were underway to ensure that all public school pupils were registered and given smart cards. The state Commissioner for Education, Mr Folorunsho Oladoyin, explained that the smart cards would contain comprehensive data of all pupils which would enable the Ministry of Education to properly monitor and track each pupil and monitor their performance in both internal and external examinations. The commissioner, according to a statement by the the information officer of the ministry on Sunday, Rose Oladoyin, spoke during a meeting with principals of government owned schools ahead of the resumption for 2020/2021 academic session. “”The smart card will go a long way in helping to monitor our students both in and outside school. We can track and monitor their academic performance at a glance because their data and everything about them can be sourced at the punch of a button,”  the statement added. Copyright PUNCH.
